---------------------------------------CSS-----------------------
inline----using style element in HTML elements

CSS syntax
selector{property:value};
who	  what	   how



display:None ----completely removes the element
visibilty:hidden ----the space of the element is kept as it is i.e. element is not completely removed

position
static--default
relative---means relative to static position which was earlier
absolute----takes top and bottom values wrt its parent element
fixed----fixed position wrt the viewport


float:left--- image on left and text on right---fits perfectly on the position besides the image
position:absolute----does not fit correctly---image comes above the text


Flex layout
parent---flex container
immediate children----flex items
